16 under the provisions of Article V of the Constitution of the United States, for the calling of
17 a convention of the states limited to proposing an amendment to the United States
18 Constitution imposing fiscal restraints on the federal government, requiring a balanced
19 budget subject to exceptions necessary to respond to emergencies and provide for the
20 national defense.
21 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that this application shall be deemed an application for a
22 convention to address only the subject herein stated. For the purposes of determining
23 whether two-thirds of the states have applied for a convention addressing any of the subjects
24 stated herein, this application is to be aggregated with the applications of any other state
25 legislatures for the single subject of balancing the federal budget, including, but not limited
26 to, previously adopted applications from Alabama, Alaska, Arizona, Arkansas, Colorado,
27 Florida, Illinois, Indiana, Iowa, Kansas, Kentucky, Louisiana, Michigan, Mississippi,
28 Missouri, Nebraska, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, North Carolina, North Dakota,
29 Ohio, Oklahoma, Oregon, Pennsylvania, South Dakota, Tennessee, Texas, Washington,
30 Utah, West Virginia, Wyoming, and Wisconsin; and this application shall be aggregated with
31 the same for the purpose of attaining the two-thirds of states necessary to require the calling
32 of a convention but shall not be aggregated with any applications on any other subject.
33 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that this application constitutes a continuing application in
34 accordance with Article V of the Constitution of the United States until the legislatures of
35 at least two-thirds of the several states have made applications on the same subject.
36 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is hereby authorized and
37 directed to make appropriate copies of this application available for distribution to the
38 President and Secretary of the United States Senate and to the Speaker and Clerk of the
39 United States House of Representatives; to the members of the United States Senate and
